The paper deals with the problem of locally correcting Boolean functions, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of juntas, which are functions that depend only on a small number of input variables, is central to the paper and is a topic in information theory (cs.IT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
